article.headline: Hartford 62, New Hampshire 46
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. (AP)Bo Taylor scored 18 points to lead Hartford to a 62-46 victory over New Hampshire Thursday, snapping an eight-game losing streak. Fabrice Tafo scored 13 points and Brian Glowiak 11 for Hartford (10-15, 4-8 America East). Radar Onguetou scored 15 points and Jermaine Anderson had 14 for New Hampshire (8-17, 4-8), which lost its fifth consecutive game. After Anderson tied the score 18-18 on a 3-pointer 13 minutes into the game, Hartford went on a 19-4 run to close out the half. Jaret Von Rosenberg capped the run on two free throws with 5.2 seconds left, giving Hartford a 37-22 lead at the break. The Hawks continued to dominate in the second half and with 6 minutes left had built a commanding 24-point lead. In their last meeting on Jan. 11, New Hampshire defeated Hartford 72-59 and made 14 three-pointers. Thursday night, Hartford held New Hampshire to just five.
